==English==
===Noun===

# '''Kung-ekoka''' ''or'' '''ǃXũ''' ''or'' '''ǃKung''', as it is often spelled in English, is a Northern [[w:Khoisan language|Khoisan language]] of [[Namibia]], [[Angola]], and [[Botswana]]. The "[[ǃ]]" in the name represents a [[w:Postalveolar click|postalveolar click]]. This language has about 5,000 speakers in the [[w:Kalahari Desert|Kalahari Desert]].


